dispatchSolutions.aircraftStatus: The oil pressure of an engine electrical generator drive is too low. The associated engine electrical generator is disconnected and must be considered inoperative.
dispatchSolutions.label: 24-21-01C
dispatchSolutions.title: Generator disconnected
dispatchSolutions.content: One may be inoperative for three flights provided that: It is checked disconnected, and The oil level of the remaining engine electrical generators is checked, and All the electrical busbars can be powered.
